description: Borrowed from French nef. Doublet of nave and nau.

entries.meaning: An extravagant table ornament and container used in the Middle Ages and Renaissance, made in the shape of a ship.

description: Short for numerically effective; introduced by Miles Reid.

entries.meaning: (algebraic geometry) Of a line bundle on a complete algebraic variety over a field: such that the degree of its restriction to every algebraic curve in the variety is non-negative.
